   CentralNotice  Massachusetts's 5th congressional district From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia 
					Jump to:					 navigation , 					 search Massachusetts's  5th congressional district Massachusetts's 5th congressional district - since January 3, 2013. Current Representative Katherine Clark   ( D – Melrose ) Cook PVI D+18 [1] Massachusetts' 5th congressional district  is a  congressional district  in eastern  Massachusetts . The district is represented by  Katherine Clark . Massachusetts congressional redistricting after the 2010 census has changed the borders of the district starting with the elections of 2012, with the new  3rd district  largely taking the place of the old 5th. [2]  The 5th district had covered many of the communities represented in the old 7th district. As of 2010, the population of the 5th congressional district was 727,515. On July 15, 2013,  Ed Markey  resigned from the seat to become the junior Senator from Massachusetts. On December 10, 2013, Democrat  Katherine Clark  won a  special election  to fill the seat for the remainder of the  113th Congress . [3]  She was sworn in to office on December 12, 2013. Contents 1   Demographics 2   Cities and towns in the district 2.1   Cities and towns in the district since 2013 2.2   Cities and towns in the district prior to 2013 2.2.1   1840s 2.2.2   1850s 2.2.3   1870s 2.2.4   1880s-1900s 2.2.5   1910s-1920s 2.2.6   1930s-1960s 2.2.7   1970s 2.2.8   2003-2013 3   Recent election results 4   List of Representatives 5   References 6   External links 6.1   Maps 6.2   Election results 